    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Gecko Layout Engine'); ?>
        <p><strong>Gecko</strong> is a web browser <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('layout engine', 'WD'); ?> used in many applications developed by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Mozilla Foundation', 'C'); ?> and the Mozilla Corporation (notably the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Firefox', 'WB'); ?> web browser including its mobile version and their e-mail client <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Thunderbird', 'WD'); ?>), as well as in many other open source software projects.</p>
        <p>Gecko is free and open-source software subject to the terms of the Mozilla Public License version 2.</p>
        <p>It is designed to support open Internet standards, and is used by different applications to display web pages and, in some cases, an application's user interface itself (by rendering <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('XUL', 'WD'); ?>).</p>
        <p>Gecko offers a rich programming <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('API', 'SD'); ?> that makes it suitable for a wide variety of roles in Internet-enabled applications, such as web browsers, content presentation, and client/server.</p>
        <p>Gecko is written in <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C++', 'languages/c'); ?> and is cross-platform, and runs on various operating systems including BSDs, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Linux', 'OS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OS X', 'OS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Solaris', 'OS'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OS/2', 'SO'); ?>, AIX, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('VMS', 'OS'); ?>, and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft Windows', 'OS'); ?>.</p>
    </div>
